@{
    ViewBag.Title = "General Dentistry";
}
<div class="container">
    <h3>@ViewBag.Title</h3><br />
    <h4>The Dental Check</h4>
    <p>We believe in offering a comprehensive assessment of oral and over all general health at our clinic.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Concerns you have about your teeth or the appearance of your teeth.</li>
        <li> General health issues which are likely going to have an impact on the oral health and dental treatment.</li>
        <li>Sings of joint disease that may effect the ability to eat or chew.</li>
        <li>Bite or occlusal discrepancy.</li>
        <li>Carry out a oral cancer screening.</li>
        <li>Signs of periodontal diseases.</li>
        <li>Help required to reach the missing area which needs cleaning so as to maintain better oral hygiene.</li>
        <li>Signs of decay.</li>
        <li>Presence of wear, erosion or cracks.</li>
        <li>Identify filling, crown or bridges etc for sign of leakage, cracks and tooth decay.</li>
        <li> Problem giving wisdom teeth.</li>
        <li>Additional x-rays required when necessary to support the finding.</li>
        <li>Treatment required, treatment options to be explained, duration of time and the cost evaluation.</li>
    </ul>
    <h4>Dental Tips</h4>
    <ul>
        <li> Visit your dentist at regular intervals depending on the individual requirement as advised by your dentist.</li>
        <li> Go for professional cleaning to maintain good oral hygiene</li>
        <li> Beware of bad breath, don't forget to clean the surface of the tongue to reduce the number of bacteria.</li>
        <li> Brush your teeth twice </li>
        <li> Use dental floss or interdental aid "good things comes in small packages". You have not properly cleaned your teeth unless you have cleaned right between them.</li>
        <li> Quit all the bad oral habits</li>
        <li> Don't substitute your precious teeth for an opener.</li>
        <li> Don't hide your crooked teeth-get a solution</li>
        <li> Always keep smiling.</li>
    </ul>
</div>






